btw at 1am last night I did a track-by-track reaction thread to the new ABBA album #ABBAVoyage bc I am one predictable gay 

if u missed it, go and have a read here‚¨áÔ∏è https://t.co/0TVBtz4bnX

Track 10 - Ode to Freedom 

This is a gentler one, has an orchestral feel - would sound fab live with a big orchestra.

As the song is at the end of the album I feel like it leaves me wanting MORE.

This one didn't quite hit the spot on first play but maybe it'll be a grower.

Track 9 - No Doubt About It

BOP ALERT. This sounds like it was recorded in the 70s but I couldn't be sure - would have to find out.

The chorus is a VERY catchy one. Verses are less so, but if I listen to them enough I'm sure they'll stick.

overall - LOVE this one.

Track 8 - Bumblebee

Probably the weakest one on the album so far - but it might grow on me. The opening reminded me of their song 'Fernando'.

It's a slow tempo one, not massively for me!

Track 7 - Keep an Eye on Dan

Who is Dan and why are we keeping an eye on them? 

First impressions - giving me pure futuristic vibes, almost like a Voulez Vous sound. You could definitely dance to this.

ALSO that last bit - LOVELY bit of sampling from S.O.S. Did you spot it?

Track 6 - I Can Be That Woman

On first impressions this gives me 'Slipping Through My Fingers' vibes. It's a ballad. I feel like it'd also be a good fit for a future Mamma Mia 3 film if there was a dramatic break up/reflective moment in the plot.

Track 5 - Just A Notion 

Recorded in the 70s, this was meant to be released during ABBA's hay day back in the day. So it feels like a musical time warp.

This a typical ABBA sound. It ends a bit bluntly with a fade out but I guess that's how most songs ended in the 70s.

Track 4 - Don't Shut Me Down 

The first lyric very cleverly leads on from the end of the last track, with another reference to children playing in a park. CLEVER.

This is an all round bop, feels like it was written about ABBA's comeback and the reaction they were hoping to get.

Track 3 - Little Things

This is a Christmas song. It has a warm feeling to it, really quite christmassy with references to children playing with new toys and warm christmassy feels.

Never thought I'd ever hear a Christmas song by ABBA. Maybe I'll listen to it all year round?!

Track 2 - When You Danced With Me 

At the start of this song I was like HMM not sure. By the end of it I was picturing myself dancing to it on that ABBA Voyage dancefloor. Seeing as ABBA are Swedish, it comes as no surprise that it has a very ‚ú®Swedish‚ú® feel. I like it a lot.

Okay am doing a song-by-song reaction 

Track 1 - I Still Have Faith in You 

Heard it before, it was their first single for this album. The thing I love the most about this one is how much it builds. Has a 'big finish' feel to it - although it's just the start of the album.
